# Core Architecture

- Keep `src/core` provider-agnostic; never import from `src/providers`.
- Use factory APIs (`createX`) with closed-over state, not classes.
- Keep contracts explicit via `...Event` interfaces and discriminated unions.
- Use `unknown` at boundaries and normalize with `toError(...)`.
- Wrap listener fan-out in `try/catch` so one consumer cannot break loops.
- Make cleanup best-effort (`disconnect/close/unsubscribe` must not mask primary failures).
- Organize files as: imports -> exported contracts -> internal constants -> factory -> private helpers.
